{'book': {'publisher': 'Harper Voyager', 'synopsis': 'Winner of the Locus Award, from award-winning and nominated editors Gardner Dozois and Jonathan Strahan, a stellar collection of the grandest, most cutting-edge epic stories in science fiction’s biggest genre—all never-before-published—by it’s most revereds practitioners and most promising newcomers.<br/>Contributors include Stephen Baxter • Greg Bear • Gregory Benford • Tony Daniel • Greg Egan • Peter F. Hamilton • M. John Harrison • James Patrick Kelly • Nancy Kress • Ken Macleod • Ian McDonald • Alastair Reynolds • Robert Silverberg • Dan Simmons • Michael Swanwick • Walter Jon Williams<br/>What sets space opera apart from other fiction is its sheer scale: it is an exuberant celebration of the very large and the very small, of the very old and the very new, of the vast, panoramic instant we live in; the instant in which everything that went before melds with everything yet to be. It is Star Wars and Battlestar Galactica.<br/>The only book of its kind, The New Space Opera brings together for the first time the generation of writers who spawned and embody the “new space opera, ” aswell as other talents destined to join their ranks. Going beyond everything that has come before, this fresh, visionary anthology is essential reading for every science fiction fan.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/67/56/9780060846756.jpg', 'title_long': 'The New Space Opera: A Hugo Award Winner', 'edition': 'First Edition', 'dimensions': 'Height: 1.03 Inches, Length: 8.98 Inches, Weight: 1.31 Pounds, Width: 6.6 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.98}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 6.6}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.31}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 1.03}}, 'pages': 517, 'date_published': '2007-06-12', 'subjects': ['Literature & Fiction', 'Genre Fiction', 'United States', 'Science Fiction & Fantasy', 'Science Fiction', 'Anthologies', 'Hard S